            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Most developers would not expect/want the expected frequency to be cut in half, as in 1a.\r\n\r\nI'm not so sure about that.  I think there will be cases where `setTimeout`-esque behavior is preferred and others where `setInterval`-esque behavior is.  I'm not sure which is better as a default, but it doesn't _really_ matter since either can be emulated with the other.\r\n\r\n> Most likely, though, no one cares.\r\n\r\nThat was my thought as well, but I wanted to make sure there was visibility on this in case people had reasons to argue otherwise.\r\n\r\n> Adjust docs if needed, but definitely include your nice (Nvim) diagrams.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure there's much to adjust.  As you already mentioned, the existing documentation doesn't guarantee any predictable behavior.  I guess calling out the `setInterval` vs. `setTimeout` difference may be useful, which should point people in the right direction to get the information that the diagrams try to convey.\r\n\r\n>  Adjust tests.\r\n\r\nPer the previous point, it's actually a bit difficult to adjust the tests.  I tried reasoning through this when merging upstream's timer tests, but either my logic was bad (entirely probable) or the unpredictable nature of it means it's just easier to treat them as inherently flaky if you're measuring timing.",
